Dear Imad,


Hope all is well.

=20

Your proposal was routed to me, as you require HPC and software. I have a c=
ouple of points that I would like to clarify with you.=20

=20

I know this may seem like a lot of questions. However, I need the informati=
on for planning and for justifying future investments in the HPC. Your help =
would be greatly appreciated.

=20
For the software, you mention Comsol and Ansys.
Firstly, do you or KU have licenses to the modules you need?
Yes, we=E2=80=99ve use them frequently.
Second, is this a commercial project? The licenses KU holds are usually Aca=
demic licenses and are not suitable for commercial projects.
No, this is not a commercial project. It is an academic project.
For the software, you mention Comsol and Ansys.=20
Do you have an estimate of the storage space you require (in TB)?
About 2 TB
Do you have an estimate of how many computing jobs you will need to run?
Difficult to say, but 200-300 to give a number.
Do you have an estimate for the average wall time of your jobs?
Also difficult to say, but 2-4 hours.
Do you have an estimate for the size of your jobs? i.e. how many cores are =
needed for each job?
About 10 cores per job.

=20

Thanks,

Dureid

=20

=20

